# Only the raw CSV is excluded -- it's 105MB+ (over/near GitHub's 100MB hard
# limit) and is NOT needed at runtime; main.py only reads the processed
# parquet files below it, all of which ARE committed despite their size
# (hotspots.parquet ~20MB, violations_clean.parquet ~19MB) because the
# deployed API loads them directly at startup and has nowhere else to get
# them without re-running the full Day 1 pipeline on every deploy.
backend/data/raw_violations.csv
backend/data/violations_exploded.parquet
backend/data/figures/

